Package: mp4encoder
Type: Package
Title: Create Uncompressed H264 Video Streams and MP4 Video Files
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Mike", "Cheng", role = c("aut", "cre", 'cph'), email = "mikefc@coolbutuseless.com")
    )
Maintainer: Mike Cheng <mikefc@coolbutuseless.com>
URL: https://github.com/coolbutuseless/mp4encoder
BugReports: https://github.com/coolbutuseless/mp4encoder/issues
Description: A video encoder which creates standard 'H.264' encoded video in 
    an 'mp4' container.  All encoding is done using base R, and no external 
    encoding libraries are used - this allows the package to work on any 
    R installation.  This package only supports uncompressed video
    streams which are very fast to create but can be large in size.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Imports:
  ctypesio (>= 0.1.2),
  bitstreamio
Suggests: 
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
Config/testthat/edition: 3
VignetteBuilder: knitr
